lass="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-405B737B-0174-4E5B-8F9D-460B9EA7D70C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_0492307DCD35442EAC71B8DA95C8A8E5" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_9CA247182A9A4603AF81EE205172E240" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Pliers 
</p></li><li id="LI_421ADE177A4748CB8EAE9311930065D8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves : 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-39CDDF45-8617-402D-89D6-95C7A354738C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0791B231-E72E-4CF0-8CE0-0CB4B1F844F8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0791B231-E72E-4CF0-8CE0-0CB4B1F844F8-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_95C2569881524C4AB0BC4EC3BCEA4C71" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-970922D6-CA69-44E1-9581-20B80D3106C3-low.png" id="IMAGE_3B9AA5916C54481FBA935BE97D92185B" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-970922D6-CA69-44E1-9581-20B80D3106C3-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_427616E2BC854A41A6E33F1B8684D8A6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_0BF2156EA25344A5ABD0556D855F2FC9" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the spring. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use the pliers or a screwdriver. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A7593949-9C02-4AB6-A5DC-E158D4AB03BD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AD35CC53-0B63-4B2B-BC75-66CB4C7DC3CF-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AD35CC53-0B63-4B2B-BC75-66CB4C7DC3CF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 4 screws in the slot holes of the motor bracket. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9717991A-597F-4E81-9BE7-A23E417CBC70" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-71F0A806-638F-4A42-A39E-6B4CE7989164-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-71F0A806-638F-4A42-A39E-6B4CE7989164-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Rotate the motor assembly clockwise to loosen and remove the drive belt. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_B03544A65269488AAEA3CF96886636A7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7E36FBC4-3D9F-4C3A-A190-C092C3387A89-low.png" id="IMAGE_B9CA56AD5E864552B9F00BAF4503F72F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7E36FBC4-3D9F-4C3A-A190-C092C3387A89-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector of the motor and the sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3E23AA85-C004-46AE-A49E-060B587B3083" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1EA4A75E-B77F-4A65-BDE3-E1DC1D7EA95C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1EA4A75E-B77F-4A65-BDE3-E1DC1D7EA95C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the motor assembly. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_1FD88EE0830847E4A2D8498764F3D5C5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B3C0B19A-43F8-4C98-89A9-855E46014910-low.png" id="IMAGE_80F0A6B8AA1F445F8A43780C71BC40AD" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B3C0B19A-43F8-4C98-89A9-855E46014910-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the bracket. 
</p><note id="GUID-4939F9A5-8581-4A3B-B02D-E39B936289D8" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">A replacement motor is always supplied with a sensor on top: So leave the sensor on. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_C981D6AD0A8942A2A1E220E16EA1BCB2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8AECEA4F-A047-418C-AA23-0F0A8DFFBB87-low.png" id="IMAGE_68727D9C7391403D8BEE1912804C25A6" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8AECEA4F-A047-418C-AA23-0F0A8DFFBB87-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_BFE8B3CE75C04146950CC3F4B903E4E0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-970922D6-CA69-44E1-9581-20B80D3106C3-low.png" id="IMAGE_1A30D19E48B940AB83780B07D9C08D62" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-970922D6-CA69-44E1-9581-20B80D3106C3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust the tension of the drive belt. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="01ADJU001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-10F0A18A-AF97-41B2-8D6D-D1AD6953ABC3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>01 How to adjust the tension of the short drive belt of the Curing carriage motor ( 01M1 ;CUR_CAR_MO)</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-22D79A6A-2191-46FA-BE14-24F47FE4288E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
